      "raw": "‍\n\nMagento (now Adobe Commerce) was once the gold standard for enterprise ecommerce SEO. Full URL control, unlimited customization, and raw technical power. But in 2025, Shopify has caught up on features while surpassing Magento on speed, maintainability, and AI readiness. Here's why enterprise brands are migrating—and what it means for SEO.\n\n‍\n\n## Where Magento Still Excels\n\nCredit where due—Magento offers:\n- **Complete URL control** — any URL structure you want\n- **Unlimited customisation** — no platform constraints\n- **Multi-store architecture** — manage multiple stores from one admin\n- **Advanced attribute management** — complex product data structures\n\nFor enterprise teams with dedicated development resources, Magento provides maximum flexibility.\n\n## Where Shopify Now Wins for SEO\n\n### Speed and Performance\n- Shopify's managed infrastructure delivers consistently fast page loads\n- Magento requires significant server optimisation to match Shopify's baseline speed\n- Core Web Vitals are easier to pass on Shopify's CDN-backed infrastructure\n\n### Total Cost of SEO\n- Magento SEO requires developer time for every change ($150-250/hour)\n- Shopify SEO can be managed through apps and AI tools without developers\n- Magento hosting costs $500-5,000/month; Shopify includes hosting\n\n### AI Tool Ecosystem\n- Shopify has 10x more AI SEO tools available\n- Shopify's API is simpler and better documented for AI integration\n- AI can programmatically update Shopify content without developer involvement\n- Magento's complexity makes AI integration more difficult and expensive\n\n### Maintenance and Security\n- Shopify handles all security patches and updates automatically\n- Magento requires ongoing maintenance, security patches, and version upgrades\n- Magento's technical debt compounds over time, slowing SEO improvements\n\n## The Migration SEO Calculation\n\nMigrating from Magento to Shopify involves SEO risk. But the calculation often favours migration:\n\n**Cost of staying on Magento (annual):**\n- Hosting: $6,000-60,000\n- Developer maintenance: $24,000-120,000\n- Security and patching: $6,000-24,000\n- SEO tool integrations: $12,000-36,000\n- **Total: $48,000-240,000/year**\n\n**Cost of Shopify + AI SEO (annual):**\n- Shopify Plus: $28,800\n- SearchFit.ai: $3,600-9,600\n- Occasional developer support: $6,000-12,000\n- **Total: $38,400-50,400/year**\n\nMost brands save 50-80% while getting faster SEO results.\n\n## Migration SEO Checklist\n\n1. **Complete URL mapping** — redirect every Magento URL to its Shopify equivalent\n2. **Content preservation** — transfer all product descriptions, meta tags, and CMS content\n3. **Schema recreation** — rebuild all structured data on Shopify\n4. **Internal link audit** — update all hardcoded links in content\n5. **301 redirect implementation** — clean redirects with no chains\n6. **Post-migration monitoring** — track indexation, rankings, and traffic for 90 days\n\n## FAQs\n\n- **Will I lose rankings migrating from Magento to Shopify?**\nShort-term fluctuation (2-4 weeks) is normal. With proper redirect mapping, most stores recover and improve within 60-90 days.\n\n- **Can Shopify handle enterprise-level SEO needs?**\nYes—Shopify Plus with AI tools handles the vast majority of enterprise SEO requirements. The few edge cases where Magento excels (complex multi-store, custom URL structures) are increasingly solvable on Shopify.\n\n- **Is Shopify's URL limitation a dealbreaker?**\nRarely. Google ranks pages based on content quality, not URL format. The `/products/` prefix doesn't meaningfully impact rankings.\n\n## Conclusion\n\nMagento served enterprise ecommerce well for a decade. But in 2025, Shopify's combination of speed, AI readiness, lower total cost, and easier maintenance makes it the better SEO platform for most brands. The migration involves short-term risk but delivers long-term SEO and business advantages.\n\nBook a demo at [https://searchfit.ai](https://searchfit.ai) or reach out to hi@searchfit.ai so we can show you how to get a 5.3% revenue increase in only 4 weeks, not months.",
